sources.title: Sherlock Holmes - Terror By Night (Film-Noir, 1936) Basil Rathbone, Nigel Bruce | Colorized
sources.description:
One way ticket to death!
Sherlock Holmes and Dr. Watson are tasked with safeguarding the Star of Rhodesia diamond on a train journey to Edinburgh, but when Roland Carstairs is murdered and the diamond stolen, Holmes suspects the notorious criminal Colonel Sebastian Moran is behind the crime and sets out to apprehend him with the help of Inspector Lestrade.

Original title: Terror by Night (1936)
This film is available with English, French, German, Italian & Spanish Audio.  And subtitles in many languages

Black & White version: https://youtu.be/C1JOyW4tNac


Director: Roy William Neill
Writers: Frank Gruber, Arthur Conan Doyle
Stars: Basil Rathbone, Nigel Bruce, Alan Mowbray 
Genres: Colorized, Literary, Crime, Drama, Film-Noir, Mystery, Thriller


00:00 Full Movie (with subtitles)

12:32 Mystery unfolds as Sherlock Holmes investigates a suspicious death on a train journey.
17:15 Investigation on a train murder mystery involving valuable gem and suspicious passengers.
21:56 Investigation of a stolen item leads to unexpected confessions and a twist involving a tea kettle.
28:29 Investigation of a stolen diamond and murder case involving Lady Carstairs and her son, with Sherlock Holmes and Dr. Watson on the case.
33:20 Investigation into suspicious activities on a train leads Sherlock Holmes to uncover a secret compartment in a coffin.
38:51 Investigation reveals hidden plot involving a stolen diamond on a train journey.

metadata.Plot: After finally catching serial killer and occult "sorcerer" Lord Blackwood, legendary sleuth Sherlock Holmes and his assistant Dr. Watson can close yet another successful case. But when Blackwood mysteriously returns from the grave and resumes his killing spree, Holmes must take up the hunt once again. Contending with his partner's new fiancée and the dimwitted head of Scotland Yard, the dauntless detective must unravel the clues that will lead him into a twisted web of murder, deceit, and black magic - and the deadly embrace of temptress Irene Adler.
metadata.Writer: Michael Robert Johnson, Anthony Peckham, Simon Kinberg
metadata.Actors: Robert Downey Jr., Jude Law, Rachel McAdams
metadata.Awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. 10 wins & 31 nominations total
